  "about": {
    "windowTitle": "01_about",
    "meta": "markdown · sh",
    "command": "cat about.md",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "main",
        "items": [
          "I work on frontend — everything visible in the browser: pages, forms, menus, user dashboards, and admin panels. I build responsive layouts with HTML, CSS, JavaScript, TypeScript, React, Angular, Vue, Svelte, Next.js, Nuxt, Tailwind, and Vite — see frontend/ in skills (12 items).",
          "I write backend code: server logic, APIs, login and user roles, databases, cache, and background jobs. I use Node.js, Python, PHP, Go, Rust, Java, C++, C#, and more; PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, MongoDB — all listed under backend/ in skills.",
          "I connect services with REST, GraphQL, WebSocket, and webhooks — payments, email, CRM, third-party APIs. In skills that is the api/ folder.",
          "I add AI — chatbots, request triage, draft text — only when doing it without AI is genuinely slower or more expensive."
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "also",
        "items": [
          "I build servers with Flask, FastAPI, Laravel, Nest.js, Express and desktop apps with Tauri and Electron — see frameworks/ in skills.",
          "I deploy with Docker, Linux, Nginx, Git, and GitHub Actions; I script with Bash and work in VS Code and Figma — the tools/ block in skills.",
          "I work with 1C:Enterprise, Accounting, document flow, and ERP when it is already part of your workflow — listed under 1c/ in skills."
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "approach",
        "items": [
          "I start by clarifying the task with you in plain language: what success looks like, who it is for, and the timeline. I ship a minimal working version, we review together, then expand without bloat.",
          "I explain key decisions, keep code readable, and hand off a project you can maintain without me.",
          "Interested? Write me via Contact — I will reply and we can talk through your task.",
          "Full stack — 49 items, see the skills section."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
